    "data": "بِسْمِ ٱللَّهِ ٱلرَّحْمَٰنِ ٱلرَّحِيمِ\nIn the name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful.\nعَبَسَ وَتَوَلَّىٰٓ (1) \nHe frowned and turned (his) back,\nأَن جَآءَهُ ٱلْأَعْمَىٰ (2) \nBecause there came to him the blind man.\nوَمَا يُدْرِيكَ لَعَلَّهُۥ يَزَّكَّىٰٓ (3) \nAnd what would make you know that he would purify himself,\nأَوْ يَذَّكَّرُ فَتَنفَعَهُ ٱلذِّكْرَىٰٓ (4) \nOr become reminded so that the reminder should profit him?\nأَمَّا مَنِ ٱسْتَغْنَىٰ (5) \nAs for him who considers himself free from need (of you),\nفَأَنتَ لَهُۥ تَصَدَّىٰ (6) \nTo him do you address yourself.\nوَمَا عَلَيْكَ أَلَّا يَزَّكَّىٰ (7) \nAnd no blame is on you if he would not purify himself\nوَأَمَّا مَن جَآءَكَ يَسْعَىٰ (8) \nAnd as to him who comes to you striving hard,\nوَهُوَ يَخْشَىٰ (9) \nAnd he fears,\nفَأَنتَ عَنْهُ تَلَهَّىٰ (10) \nFrom him will you divert yourself.\nكَلَّآ إِنَّهَا تَذْكِرَةٌ (11) \nNay! surely it is an admonishment.\nفَمَن شَآءَ ذَكَرَهُۥ (12) \nSo let him who pleases mind it.\nفِى صُحُفٍ مُّكَرَّمَةٍ (13) \nIn honored books,\nمَّرْفُوعَةٍ مُّطَهَّرَةٍۭ (14) \nExalted, purified,\nبِأَيْدِى سَفَرَةٍ (15) \nIn the hands of scribes\nكِرَامٍۭ بَرَرَةٍ (16) \nNoble, virtuous.\nقُتِلَ ٱلْإِنسَٰنُ مَآ أَكْفَرَهُۥ (17) \nCursed be man! how ungrateful is he!\nمِنْ أَىِّ شَىْءٍ خَلَقَهُۥ (18) \nOf what thing did He create him?\nمِن نُّطْفَةٍ خَلَقَهُۥ فَقَدَّرَهُۥ (19) \nOf a small seed; He created him, then He made him according to a measure,\nثُمَّ ٱلسَّبِيلَ يَسَّرَهُۥ (20) \nThen (as for) the way-- He has made it easy (for him)\nثُمَّ أَمَاتَهُۥ فَأَقْبَرَهُۥ (21) \nThen He causes him to die, then assigns to him a grave,\nثُمَّ إِذَا شَآءَ أَنشَرَهُۥ (22) \nThen when He pleases, He will raise him to life again.\nكَلَّا لَمَّا يَقْضِ مَآ أَمَرَهُۥ (23) \nNay; but he has not done what He bade him.\nفَلْيَنظُرِ ٱلْإِنسَٰنُ إِلَىٰ طَعَامِهِۦٓ (24) \nThen let man look to his food,\nأَنَّا صَبَبْنَا ٱلْمَآءَ صَبًّا (25) \nThat We pour down the water, pouring (it) down in abundance,\nثُمَّ شَقَقْنَا ٱلْأَرْضَ شَقًّا (26) \nThen We cleave the earth, cleaving (it) asunder,\nفَأَنۢبَتْنَا فِيهَا حَبًّا (27) \nThen We cause to grow therein the grain,\nوَعِنَبًا وَقَضْبًا (28) \nAnd grapes and clover,\nوَزَيْتُونًا وَنَخْلًا (29) \nAnd the olive and the palm,\nوَحَدَآئِقَ غُلْبًا (30) \nAnd thick gardens,\nوَفَٰكِهَةً وَأَبًّا (31) \nAnd fruits and herbage\nمَّتَٰعًا لَّكُمْ وَلِأَنْعَٰمِكُمْ (32) \nA provision for you and for your cattle.\nفَإِذَا جَآءَتِ ٱلصَّآخَّةُ (33) \nBut when the deafening cry comes,\nيَوْمَ يَفِرُّ ٱلْمَرْءُ مِنْ أَخِيهِ (34) \nThe day on which a man shall fly from his brother,\nوَأُمِّهِۦ وَأَبِيهِ (35) \nAnd his mother and his father,\nوَصَٰحِبَتِهِۦ وَبَنِيهِ (36) \nAnd his spouse and his son--\nلِكُلِّ ٱمْرِئٍ مِّنْهُمْ يَوْمَئِذٍ شَأْنٌ يُغْنِيهِ (37) \nEvery man of them shall on that day have an affair which will occupy him.\nوُجُوهٌ يَوْمَئِذٍ مُّسْفِرَةٌ (38) \n(Many) faces on that day shall be bright,\nضَاحِكَةٌ مُّسْتَبْشِرَةٌ (39) \nLaughing, joyous.\nوَوُجُوهٌ يَوْمَئِذٍ عَلَيْهَا غَبَرَةٌ (40) \nAnd (many) faces on that day, on them shall be dust,\nتَرْهَقُهَا قَتَرَةٌ (41) \nDarkness shall cover them.\nأُو۟لَٰٓئِكَ هُمُ ٱلْكَفَرَةُ ٱلْفَجَرَةُ (42) \nThese are they who are unbelievers, the wicked.", 
    "title": "80: Abasa عبس"
}